[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    388[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     model.Maximize(sum(objective_terms))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    389[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    390[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return model, x, patients, beds
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    391[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    392[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    393[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    394[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    395[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 4: Solve and Extract Recommendations
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    396[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    397[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `solve_and_recommend(model, state, solve_time_limit_seconds)`. Run the solver, check the result status, and translate the mathematical solution back into human-readable bed assignments.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    398[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    399[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    400[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def solve_assignment(model, x, patients, beds) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    401[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    402[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Run the CP-SAT solver and extract the recommended assignments.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    403[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    404[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The solver explores the space of valid assignments and finds the one
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    405[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     that maximizes our weighted objective. For typical hospital sizes
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    406[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     (20-40 pending patients, 50-100 available beds), this takes 1-3 seconds.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    407[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
